---
title: Steak & Shallot Pan Sauce with Garlic Bread & Roasted Zucchini
description: A drizzle of buttery pan sauce takes perfectly-cooked steaks from good to mind-blowing. After the meat is seared, we use those precious pan drippings to create a silky, aromatic sauce that’s beefed up with rich broth, finely chopped shallot, and a pat of butter. It’s all served with garlic bread and roasted zucchini for a complete (and dare we say elegant?) meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/steak-shallot-pan-sauce-f1964886.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/steak-shallot-pan-sauce-5f0497b65ad26e2f211dff34-93490b75.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 38 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1120 mg
time required: 25m
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/steak-shallot-pan-sauce-5f0497b65ad26e2f211dff34
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise
into ½-inch-thick rounds. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve, peel,
and finely chop @shallot{1}. Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes}
(you'll add the garlic bread then).

Meanwhile, place 1 TBSP @butter{1%tbsp} and garlic in a small
#microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until softened, ~{10%seconds}. Spread onto cut
sides of baguette; season with salt and pepper. Once zucchini has roasted 12
minutes, carefully toss and push to one side of #baking sheet{}. Place garlic
bread cut sides up on empty side.

> For 4 servings, leave zucchini roasting; add bread to a second baking sheet
and toast on middle rack.

Roast until zucchini is tender and bread is toasted, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

While garlic bread toasts, pat @ranch steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{};
season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a
#large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness,
~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside to rest.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add
shallot and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}. Stir in
@beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook,
scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until reduced by half,
~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and
pepper.

Halve garlic bread on a diagonal if desired. Divide steak, zucchini, and garlic
bread between #plates{}. Top steak with sauce and serve.